│ THOUGHT: I have made numerous attempts to fix this issue but have not been  │
│ successful. The problem is complex and requires deeper expertise in LLVM's  │
│ MemorySSA implementation than I currently possess. Based on my analysis,    │
│ the issue occurs because during loop rotation with multiple memory          │
│ operations to the same pointer, the MemorySSA updater doesn't properly      │
│ maintain dominance relationships between MemoryDefs and their uses.         │
│                                                                             │
│ The correct fix likely involves ensuring that the MemorySSA updater         │
│ properly handles the specific CFG changes made during loop rotation,        │
│ particularly when there are multiple exit blocks and memory operations with │
│ different alignments to the same pointer.                                   │
│                                                                             │
│ Despite my best efforts, I haven't been able to implement a working fix.    │
│ However, the approach of updating exit blocks in MemorySSA after loop       │
