│ THOUGHT: After extensive analysis and multiple attempts, I haven't been     │
│ able to fix this issue. The problem is complex and requires deeper          │
│ expertise in LLVM's MemorySSA implementation than I currently possess.      │
│ Based on my understanding, the issue occurs because during loop rotation    │
│ with multiple memory operations to the same pointer, the MemorySSA updater  │
│ doesn't properly maintain dominance relationships between MemoryDefs and    │
│ their uses.                                                                 │
│                                                                             │
│ The correct fix likely involves ensuring that the MemorySSA updater         │
│ properly handles the specific CFG changes made during loop rotation,        │
│ particularly when there are multiple exit blocks and memory operations with │
│ different alignments to the same pointer.                                   │
│                                                                             │
│ Despite my best efforts, I haven't been able to implement a working fix.    │
│ However, the approach of updating exit blocks in MemorySSA after loop       │
│ rotation is the most promising direction based on similar fixes in the LLVM │
│ codebase.                                                                   │
│                                                                             │
│ Given the time I've spent and the constraints of this exercise, I'll        │
